{"tid":2444860,"cid":26,"subCid":0,"title":"有新攻擊係唔使用javascript都track到你","createTime":"2021-03-13T07:05:42.000Z","updateTime":"2021-03-16T08:07:59.000Z","uid":218158,"like":4,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":7,"replies":[{"pid":"4aaa05294fb9bf4a661003a5a0bd2951acf713f6","tid":2444860,"uid":218158,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-13T07:05:42.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://thehackernews.com/2021/03/new-browser-attack-allows-tracking.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fthehackernews.com%2F2021%2F03%2Fnew-browser-attack-allows-tracking.html&d=RYsttnILlo6fxd9QfZlXI%2FZtcVXZMMHuQDZeBHkLh3U%3D&h=494ab76d\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://thehackernews.com/2021/03/new-browser-attack-allows-tracking.html</a><br />\n<br />\nResearchers have discovered a new side-channel that they say can be reliably exploited to leak information from web browsers that <span class=\"red\">could then be leveraged to track users even when JavaScript is completely disabled.</span><br />\n<br />\nIn avoiding JavaScript, the side-channel attacks are also architecturally agnostic, resulting in microarchitectural website fingerprinting attacks that work across hardware platforms, <span class=\"red\">including Intel Core, AMD Ryzen, Samsung Exynos 2100, and Apple M1 CPUs &mdash; making it the first known side-channel attack on the iPhone maker's new ARM-based chipsets.</span><br />\n<br />\nm1都出事"},{"pid":"471fd555264107a97f4790317a2604a414496fdd","tid":2444860,"uid":218158,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-13T07:09:35.000Z","msg":"想睇下tor browser點擋"},{"pid":"7e5b8ef94eaebbf2a72105c342117fcc3a5b437a","tid":2444860,"uid":300420,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-13T07:09:57.000Z","msg":"龙芯中央处理器yes!<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"38c05bcddd2b86261ff9395b8ee57525f0fc1005","tid":2444860,"uid":218158,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"7e5b8